President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in the State of Tennessee and has authorized Federal aid to support recovery efforts in areas affected by severe storms, straight-line winds, and tornadoes from March 1 to March 3, 2023. The Federal funding will be available to State and eligible local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, on a cost-sharing basis. The funds will be used for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in various counties. Additionally, Federal funding will also be available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Mr. Andrew D. Friend of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made in the future if requested by the State and based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.